12 * * *
13 § 1272. SEVERANCE AND BENEFIT EXTENSION AGREEMENTS;
14 AVAILABILITY FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION AND COPYING
15 (a) As used in this section:
16 (1) “Benefit extension agreements” means an agreement made between
17 a State public agency and an employee that confers severance pay or the
18 extension of an employment benefit beyond the date of separation.
19 (2) “Public agency” means a “public agency” as defined by 1 V.S.A.
20 § 317.
