1 (b) Benefit extension agreements shall be available for public inspection
2 and copying pursuant to Vermont’s Public Records Act.
3 (c) Annually, on or before July 1, every public agency of the State shall
4 publish an annual report concerning all benefit extension agreements executed
5 by the public agency during the preceding fiscal year. The annual report shall
6 contain:
7 (1) the names and positions of the individuals receiving benefits under a
8 benefit extension agreement;
9 (2) the total amount paid to each individual pursuant to a benefit
10 extension agreement;
11 (3) a list of the specific employment benefits conferred to each
12 individual under a benefit extension agreement;
13 (4) the duration of each benefit extension agreement; and
14 (5) the reasons for employment termination for each individual who
15 receives benefits pursuant to a benefit extension agreement.
16 Sec. 4. REPORTS; BENEFIT EXTENSION AGREEMENTS FOR THE
17 YEARS 2018 THROUGH 2025
18 On or before January 15, 2026, each public agency of the State shall publish
19 a report containing the information required by 32 V.S.A. § 1272(c) for the
20 years 2018 through 2025.
